I"}<p>The process of feature selection, also known as variable selection, attribute selection or variable subset selection is a core component of machine learning (ML) and statistical modeling. Feature selection techniques are usefull in:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Reducing the undelying complexity of the machine learning/statistical model [1],</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Sorter training/convergence times for the machine learning/statistical model [2],</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Avoid the curse of dimensonality problem by removing irrelavent features from the data [2].</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>Feature selection assumes that there are a few features in the data can be reddundant or irrelavent for the prediction and hence can be removed without incurring much deviation in the performance of the model.</p>

